(7, 1, 'In Tradeback RBY, the Elemental Punches are wonderful.\nAlakazam and Gengar can hit Starmie and Exeggutor in their weakness, Electabuzz wins Ice Punch to deal with Graveler, Magmar now has Thunder Punch...\n\nIn RBY Only, the Elemental Punches have a very limited distribution, and the Pokémon learning them either have better options (Blizzard for Jynx, Thunderbolt for Electabuzz, Fire Blast for Magmar), or have no need for them (Hitmonchan).', 'Fire Blast has 120 Power, 85% accuracy, 8PP and a 30% chance to Burn the target, which can be either wonderful against Golem and Snorlax, or a disaster against Starmie.\n\nFlamethrower on the other hand has 95 Power, 99.6% accuracy, 24PP and a 10% chance to Burn the target.\n\nFire moves in Top and High Tiers are only seen as a universal counter to some popular leads such as Jynx and Exeggutor, as it is their only advantage over Ice moves in these Tiers.', 2),
(7, 2, '', '', 2),
(8, 1, 'In Tradeback RBY, the Elemental Punches are wonderful.\nAlakazam and Gengar can hit Starmie and Exeggutor in their weakness, Electabuzz wins Ice Punch to deal with Graveler, Magmar now has Thunder Punch...\n\nIn RBY Only, the Elemental Punches have a very limited distribution, and the Pokémon learning them either have better options (Blizzard for Jynx, Thunderbolt for Electabuzz, Fire Blast for Magmar), or have no need for them (Hitmonchan).', 'Blizzard has 120 Power, 90% accuracy, 8PP and a 10% chance to Freeze the target.\n\nIce Beam has 95 Power, 99.6% accuracy, 16PP and a 10% chance to Freeze the target.', 2),
(8, 2, '', '', 2),
