(143, 1, 'It has some use on Aerodactyl and Articuno.\nOn Aerodactyl, you use your great speed to send Aerodactyl threaten a weakened Pokémon, forcing it to switch-out, and charge Sky Attack during the time they switch out so you can hit very hard on the next turn. This requires that Rocks and Electrics are out of the way of course.\n\nOn Articuno, you can send it on a predicted Earthquake from Golem / Rhydon, and charge Sky Attack as they switch out their Golem / Rhydon. If their Starmie is weakened and they send it out, they will send back Golem / Rhydon take the Sky Attack, and you will chirp away 15~20% of their HPs (30~38 on a Critical Hit). This can pay off after a few uses as they let their Golem / Rhydon in thinking that you will use Sky Attack once again, only to get pummeled by a powerful Blizzard / Ice Beam.', 'Drill Peck has 80 Power and does not require a charging turn.', 2),
